        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38447",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There is no difference to\r\n{quote}\r\nprint new Zend_Date('10\/03\/2010')->get(Zend_Date::MONTH);\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nAs you can have multiple instances of this object the factory pattern is not necessary.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-13T15:06:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-13T15:06:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38453",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yegor256",
                        "name": "yegor256",
                        "displayName": "Yegor Bugayenko",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "such syntax is not allowed in PHP",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yegor256",
                        "name": "yegor256",
                        "displayName": "Yegor Bugayenko",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-15T00:20:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-15T00:20:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38475",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yegor256",
                        "name": "yegor256",
                        "displayName": "Yegor Bugayenko",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "maybe a parameter to now() would help? for example:\r\n\r\necho Zend_Date::now('10\/03\/2010')->get(Zend_Date::MONTH);\r\n\r\nwhat do you think?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yegor256",
                        "name": "yegor256",
                        "displayName": "Yegor Bugayenko",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-16T01:03:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-16T01:03:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38476",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thymus",
                        "name": "thymus",
                        "displayName": "Raphael Dehousse",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I would rather prefer the factory method then.\r\nBecause, for me, now will return the current Zend_Date, and I won't think that I would pass a param to now() to receive another date.\r\nAnd also, the factory method could have all the params of Zend_Date constructor.\r\n\r\nLike that, we could do\r\n\r\n Zend_Date::factory('2010\/01\/01', 'yyyy\/dd\/MM', $locale)->get(Zend_Date::MONTH);\r\n\r\netc\r\n\r\nMy 2 cents,",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thymus",
                        "name": "thymus",
                        "displayName": "Raphael Dehousse",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-16T01:28:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-16T01:28:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38562",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I still see no reason to add what's already working into a class which will be completly changed in the next release.\r\n\r\nActually it simply works with:\r\n\r\necho Zend_Date::now()->set('2010\/01\/01', 'yyyy\/dd\/MM', $locale)->get(Zend_Date::MONTH);",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-18T15:18:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-18T15:18:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38563",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Additionally a date filter is already accepted and will be added with the next minor release which itself simplifies the handling much more.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-18T15:19:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-18T15:19:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38567",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yegor256",
                        "name": "yegor256",
                        "displayName": "Yegor Bugayenko",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "How exactly I can create an object and get its string value in one command? Could you please give a code example? Thanks.",
